BILL NO. 1975 By: McIntosh, Grellner, and
2 Jett of the Senate
3 and
4 Miller of the House
5
6 An Act relating to schools; amending 70 O.S. 2021,
Section 1210.704, as amended by Section 20, Chapter
7 323, O.S.L. 2023 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
1210.704), which relates to advanced placement
8 courses; requiring public school districts to make
certain examinations available to certain students;
9 requiring districts to post certain information about
the examinations on their websites; directing certain
10 online learning platform to be available to all
students in the state; providing an effective date;
11 and declaring an emergency.
12
13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 70 O.S. 2021, Section 1210.704, as
15 amended by Section 20, Chapter 323, O.S.L. 2023 (70 O.S. Supp. 2025,
16 Section 1210.704), is amended to read as follows:
17 Section 1210.704. A. Beginning with the 2024–2025 school year,
18 all public high schools in this state shall make a minimum of four
19 advanced placement courses available to students.
20 B. School district boards of education shall be responsible for
21 ensuring annually that all high school students have access to
22 advanced placement courses beginning in the 2024-2025 school year.
23 Such access may be provided through enrollment in courses offered
24 through:
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1975 Page 1

1 1. A school site or sites within the district;
2 2. A technology center school within the district;
3 3. An online learning program offered by the Statewide Charter
4 School Board or one of its vendors; or
5 4. A school site or sites in another school district.
6 C. Each public school district in this state shall make
7 advanced placement examinations available each school year to any
8 student who resides in the district. No later than August 31 of
9 each year, each school district shall post on its website notice of
10 the date each advanced placement examination is to be administered.
11 The notice shall state that the examination is available to students
12 who reside in the district and shall include registration dates and
13 procedures to register for the examination.
14 D. The Statewide Charter School Board shall maintain an online
15 learning platform to provide high quality online learning
16 opportunities for Oklahoma students that are aligned with the
17 subject matter standards adopted by the State Board of Education
18 pursuant to Section 11-103.6 of this title. The Board shall
19 implement online courses, with an emphasis on science, technology,
20 engineering, and math (STEM) courses, foreign language courses, and
21 advanced placement courses. The online platform shall be available
22 to all Oklahoma school districts students in this state.
23 D. E. The State Department of Education shall provide
24 information to all boards of education, to be distributed to their
ENGR. S. B. NO. 1975 Page 2

1 stud ents and parents, on available opportunities and the enrollment
2 process for students to take advanced placement courses. The
3 information shall explain the value of advanced placement courses in
4 preparing students for postsecondary-level coursework, enabling
5 students to gain access to postsecondary opportunities, and
6 qualifying for scholarships and other financial aid opportunities.
7 E. F. The State Department of Education shall retain records of
8 which options outlined in subsection B of this section boards of
9 education selected for their students and make the information
10 available on the Department’s website.
11 F. G. As used in this section, “advanced placement course”
12 shall have the same meaning as provided in paragraph 1 of Section
13 1210.702 of this title.
14 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2026.
15 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
16 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
17 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
18 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
